\n  1338\\\\t\\\\n  1339\\\\t            # Y/X handled globally above\\\\n  1340\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_TL:      # L bumper → seek back (accel)\\\\n  1341\\\\t                self.accel.press(\\\\\\\"seek_bwd\\\\\\\")\\\\n  1342\\\\t\\\\n  1343\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_TR:      # R bumper → seek forward (accel)\\\\n  1344\\\\t                self.accel.press(\\\\\\\"seek_fwd\\\\\\\")\\\\n  1345\\\\t\\\\n  1346\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_START:   # + → play/pause\\\\n  1347\\\\t                if not _mpris_play_pause():\\\\n  1348\\\\t                    self.vinput.key_tap(ecodes.KEY_SPACE)\\\\n  1349\\\\t\\\\n  1350\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_SELECT:  # - → Tab\\\\n  1351\\\\t                self.vinput.key_tap(ecodes.KEY_TAB)\\\\n  1352\\\\t\\\\n  1353\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_THUMBL:  # L stick click → Enter\\\\n  1354\\\\t                self.vinput.key_tap(ecodes.KEY_ENTER)\\\\n  1355\\\\t\\\\n  1356\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_THUMBR:  # R stick click → right-click\\\\n  1357\\\\t                self.vinput.key_tap(ecodes.BTN_RIGHT)\\\\n  1358\\\\t\\\\n  1359\\\\t            elif code == ecodes.BTN_TL2:     # ZL → toggle fullscreen (universal)\\\\n  1360\\\\t                self.is_fullscreen = not self.is_fullscreen\\\\n  1361\\\\t                if not _mpv_command([\\\\\\\"cycle\\\\\\\", \\\\\\\"fullscreen\\\\\\\"]):\\\\n  1362\\\\t                    self.vinput.key_tap(ecodes.KEY_F11)\\\\n  1363\\\\t                log(f\\\\\\\"Fullscreen toggled: {self.is_fullscreen}\\\\\\\")\\\\n  1364\\\\t\\\\n  1365\\\\t    def _handle_button_release(self, code):\\\\n  1366\\\\t        \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"Handle button release events for held-state buttons.\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\\\\"\\\\n  1367\\\\t        # Release accelerating hold actions\\\\n  1368\\\\t        if code == ecodes.BTN_TL:\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_31\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing focus and potential bugs**\\\\n\\\\nI'm considering how the root AppWindow has a wrapping FocusScope, which might take focus away from the child if it's created afterward. The child might only run its `init` method during construction, especially if it appears and disappears based on screens. There seems to be a definite bug in the `on_navigate` detail related to token authentication. If there's an auth error, it fails and incorrectly sets an error. I need to examine the loading overlay callback since it interacts with the AppBridge’s properties, which could lead to issues if the network is slow!\\\\n**Identifying performance issues**\\\\n\\\\nI'm analyzing an execution contract that addresses one issue per iteration. The highest priority seems to stem from the code and logs. It looks like the loading hang might be caused by concurrent duplicate detail loads without any guard or cancellation. I could improve this by introducing request token generation and stale request cancellation, which might also help with user login hangs. I need to gather evidence from the code, especially exploring how `on_navigate` and `on_login` spawn async tasks without guards. Repeated key presses could lead to excessive tasks, spiking memory usage. I think I can minimize this by adding a gate to prevent re-entrant navigation while loading!\\\\n**Investigating the loading screen issue**\\\\n\\\\nI’m analyzing the issue where selecting any media item leads to a permanent loading black screen, even with a single press. This might be happening because the callback is re-entering due to home events being emitted from both the content-row and the card, potentially causing duplicate callbacks! I'll need to inspect the event chain for both the content-row and the card to see if the key press triggers both. I should check the content-row key handler to ensure it doesn’t handle both the Return and item-selected actions simultaneously, which could lead to multiple triggers. Let's dive into content-row.slint!\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.started\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_32\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"nl -ba ui/content-row.slint | sed -n '1,260p'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":null,\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_32\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"nl -ba ui/content-row.slint | sed -n '1,260p'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"     1\\\\t// Jellyfin Pi TV App - Content Row Component\\\\n     2\\\\t// Horizontal scrolling row of MediaCards (Jellyfin Android TV home screen style)\\\\n     3\\\\t\\\\n     4\\\\timport { Theme, MediaItem } from \\\\\\\"theme.slint\\\\\\\";\\\\n     5\\\\timport { MediaCard } from \\\\\\\"card.slint\\\\\\\";\\\\n     6\\\\t\\\\n     7\\\\texport component ContentRow inherits VerticalLayout {\\\\n     8\\\\t    in property <string> title: \\\\\\\"\\\\\\\";\\\\n     9\\\\t    in property <[MediaItem]> items: [];\\\\n    10\\\\t    in property <bool> is-landscape: false;\\\\n    11\\\\t    in-out property <bool> row-focused: false;\\\\n    12\\\\t    in-out property <int> focused-index: 0;\\\\n    13\\\\t\\\\n    14\\\\t    callback item-selected(string);\\\\n    15\\\\t    callback item-play-requested(string);\\\\n    16\\\\t\\\\n    17\\\\t    private property <length> card-width: root.is-landscape ? Theme.landscape-width : Theme.poster-width;\\\\n    18\\\\t    private property <length> scroll-target: root.focused-index * (root.card-width + Theme.card-gap);\\\\n    19\\\\t\\\\n    20\\\\t    spacing: 0px;\\\\n    21\\\\t\\\\n    22\\\\t    // Row title\\\\n    23\\\\t    Text {\\\\n    24\\\\t        text: root.title;\\\\n    25\\\\t        font-size: Theme.font-title-medium;\\\\n    26\\\\t        font-weight: 700;\\\\n    27\\\\t        color: root.row-focused ? Theme.text-primary : Theme.text-secondary;\\\\n    28\\\\t        horizontal-alignment: left;\\\\n    29\\\\t\\\\n    30\\\\t        animate color {\\\\n    31\\\\t            duration: Theme.focus-duration;\\\\n    32\\\\t        }\\\\n    33\\\\t    }\\\\n    34\\\\t\\\\n    35\\\\t    // Spacer between title and cards\\\\n    36\\\\t    Rectangle {\\\\n    37\\\\t        height: 8px;\\\\n    38\\\\t    }\\\\n    39\\\\t\\\\n    40\\\\t    // Horizontal scrolling card strip\\\\n    41\\\\t    Flickable {\\\\n    42\\\\t        height: root.is-landscape ? Theme.landscape-height + 120px : Theme.poster-height + 120px;\\\\n    43\\\\t        viewport-width: max(self.width, root.items.length * (root.card-width + Theme.card-gap) + Theme.overscan-h * 2);\\\\n    44\\\\t\\\\n    45\\\\t        viewport-x: -root.scroll-target + Theme.overscan-h;\\\\n    46\\\\t\\\\n    47\\\\t        animate viewport-x {\\\\n    48\\\\t            duration: Theme.transition-duration;\\\\n    49\\\\t            easing: ease-in-out;\\\\n    50\\\\t        }\\\\n    51\\\\t\\\\n    52\\\\t        HorizontalLayout {\\\\n    53\\\\t            spacing: Theme.card-gap;\\\\n    54\\\\t            padding-left: Theme.overscan-h;\\\\n    55\\\\t            padding-right: Theme.overscan-h;\\\\n    56\\\\t\\\\n    57\\\\t            for item[index] in root.items : MediaCard {\\\\n    58\\\\t                item: item;\\\\n    59\\\\t                is-landscape: root.is-landscape;\\\\n    60\\\\t                focused: root.row-focused && index == root.focused-index;\\\\n    61\\\\t\\\\n    62\\\\t                selected(id) => {\\\\n    63\\\\t                    root.item-selected(id);\\\\n    64\\\\t                }\\\\n    65\\\\t            }\\\\n    66\\\\t        }\\\\n    67\\\\t    }\\\\n    68\\\\t\\\\n    69\\\\t    // Focus scope for keyboard/gamepad navigation\\\\n    70\\\\t    FocusScope {\\\\n    71\\\\t        width: 0px;\\\\n    72\\\\t        height: 0px;\\\\n    73\\\\t        enabled: root.row-focused;\\\\n    74\\\\t\\\\n    75\\\\t        key-pressed(event) => {\\\\n    76\\\\t            if (event.text == Key.RightArrow) {\\\\n    77\\\\t                if (root.focused-index < root.items.length - 1) {\\\\n    78\\\\t                    root.focused-index += 1;\\\\n    79\\\\t                }\\\\n    80\\\\t                return accept;\\\\n    81\\\\t            }\\\\n    82\\\\t            if (event.text == Key.LeftArrow) {\\\\n    83\\\\t                if (root.focused-index > 0) {\\\\n    84\\\\t                    root.focused-index -= 1;\\\\n    85\\\\t                }\\\\n    86\\\\t                return accept;\\\\n    87\\\\t            }\\\\n    88\\\\t            if (event.text == Key.Return || event.text == \\\\\\\" \\\\\\\") {\\\\n    89\\\\t                if (root.focused-index >= 0 && root.focused-index < root.items.length) {\\\\n    90\\\\t                    root.item-selected(root.items[root.focused-index].id);\\\\n    91\\\\t                }\\\\n    92\\\\t                return accept;\\\\n    93\\\\t            }\\\\n    94\\\\t            return reject;\\\\n    95\\\\t        }\\\\n    96\\\\t    }\\\\n    97\\\\t}\\\\n\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":0,\\\"status\\\":\\\"completed\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_33\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"reasoning\\\",\\\"text\\\":\\\"**Analyzing focus scopes**\\\\n\\\\nI’m noticing that both HomeScreen FocusScope and ContentRow FocusScope manage Return and item-selected events. If both scopes receive a key due to the focus chain, there might be a duplicate event, especially if content-row focus is enabled. The focus scope size might complicate things further. I'm concerned that pressing “A” could trigger multiple navigation calls quickly, leading to duplicate loads and possibly endless loading issues. I should also check the login screen for similar focus scope issues causing multiple login attempts. Let’s take a closer look at login.slint for key handlers.\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.started\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_34\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"rg -n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"FocusScope|Key.Return|select-user\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(|submit-password\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(|login\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" ui/login.slint | sed -n '1,200p'; nl -ba ui/login.slint | sed -n '500,700p'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"\\\",\\\"exit_code\\\":null,\\\"status\\\":\\\"in_progress\\\"}}\\n{\\\"type\\\":\\\"item.completed\\\",\\\"item\\\":{\\\"id\\\":\\\"item_34\\\",\\\"type\\\":\\\"command_execution\\\",\\\"command\\\":\\\"/bin/zsh -lc \\\\\\\"rg -n \\\\\\\\\\\\\\\"FocusScope|Key.Return|select-user\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(|submit-password\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(|login\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\(\\\\\\\\\\\\\\\" ui/login.slint | sed -n '1,200p'; nl -ba ui/login.slint | sed -n '500,700p'\\\\\\\"\\\",\\\"aggregated_output\\\":\\\"148:    callback select-user(string);\\\\n149:    callback submit-password(string, string);\\\\n529:    key-handler := FocusScope {\\\\n548:                if (event.text == Key.Return) {\\\\n558:                            root.select-user(root.users[root.focused-user].id);\\\\n603:                if (event.text == Key.Return) {\\\\n625:                            root.submit-password(root.selected-user-id, root.password-input);\\\\n   500\\\\t                    vertical-alignment: center;\\\\n   501\\\\t                }\\\\n   502\\\\t            }\\\\n   503\\\\t        }\\\\n   504\\\\t\\\\n   505\\\\t        Text {\\\\n   506\\\\t            text: \\\\\\\"Authorize this code in your Jellyfin app\\\\\\\";\\\\n   507\\\\t            font-size: Theme.font-body-medium;\\\\n   508\\\\t            color: Theme.text-secondary;\\\\n   509\\\\t            horizontal-alignment: center;\\\\n   510\\\\t        }\\\\n   511\\\\t\\\\n   512\\\\t        HorizontalLayout {\\\\n 